––– comment –––
Test Sharding plugin auth: user-facing permission gating for sharded tables.
Issue: https://github.com/manticoresoftware/dev/issues/2735
Admin credentials: admin / adminpass (bootstrap via auth.json)

Daemon gates every parseable statement itself (unprefixed sharded CREATE/DROP,
SELECT, etc). Cluster-prefixed sharded CREATE/DROP fail to parse daemon-side,
so Buddy gates them via a daemon-evaluated probe (bare ALTER TABLE) on the
user-delegated client. SHOW SHARDING STATUS/MASTER are filtered through the
daemon's permission-filtered SHOW TABLES: a user only sees sharded tables
they have grants on.
––– comment –––
––– block: ../base/start-searchd-with-auth –––
––– comment –––
––– Setup: create user alice with no grants –––
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -E -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE USER 'alice' IDENTIFIED BY 'alicepass123';"
––– output –––
*************************** 1. row ***************************
       token: #!/[0-9a-f]{64}/!#
    username: alice
generated_at: #!/([0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2} [0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2}|[A-Z][a-z]{2} [A-Z][a-z]{2} [ 0-9][0-9] [0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2}\.[0-9]{3} [0-9]{4})/!#
––– comment –––
––– 1. admin creates a local sharded table –––
EXPECTED: Success
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE TABLE shop(id bigint) shards='2' rf='1';"; echo $?
––– output –––
0
––– input –––
sleep 2; echo done
––– output –––
done
––– comment –––
––– 2. alice without grants: daemon denies unprefixed sharded CREATE –––
EXPECTED: Permission denied (daemon-side gate, never reaches Buddy)
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=alicepass123 mysql -ualice -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE TABLE x1(id bigint) shards='2' rf='1';"
––– output –––
ERROR 1045 (42000) at line 1: Permission denied for user 'alice'
––– comment –––
––– 3. alice without grants: SHOW SHARDING STATUS/MASTER are empty –––
EXPECTED: Empty result, no topology leak
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=alicepass123 mysql -ualice -h0 -P9306 -e "SHOW SHARDING STATUS;"; echo $?
––– output –––
0
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=alicepass123 mysql -ualice -h0 -P9306 -e "SHOW SHARDING MASTER;"; echo $?
––– output –––
0
––– comment –––
––– 4. admin sees the full sharding topology –––
EXPECTED: 2 shard rows for shop, active master
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "SHOW SHARDING STATUS;" | grep -c shop
––– output –––
2
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "SHOW SHARDING MASTER;" | grep -c active
––– output –––
1
––– comment –––
––– 5. cluster-prefixed path: Buddy gates what the daemon cannot parse –––
EXPECTED: alice denied by Buddy probe gate; admin passes the gate and
fails later on single-node cluster validation
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "GRANT replication ON * TO 'admin';"
––– output –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE CLUSTER c;"; echo $?
––– output –––
0
––– input –––
sleep 2; echo done
––– output –––
done
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=alicepass123 mysql -ualice -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE TABLE c:atbl(id bigint) shards='2' rf='1';"
––– output –––
ERROR 1064 (42000) at line 1: Permission denied for user 'alice': requires schema permission on table 'atbl'
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=alicepass123 mysql -ualice -h0 -P9306 -e "DROP TABLE c:ghost;"
––– output –––
ERROR 1064 (42000) at line 1: Permission denied for user 'alice': requires schema permission on table 'ghost'
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE TABLE c:rtbl(id bigint) shards='2' rf='1';"
––– output –––
ERROR 1064 (42000) at line 1: The node count for cluster c is too low: 1. You can create local sharded table.
––– comment –––
––– 6. granted flow: schema on 'mall' lets alice create it –––
EXPECTED: create succeeds, but schema alone gives no visibility:
SHOW SHARDING STATUS/MASTER follow the daemon-filtered SHOW TABLES,
which requires read permission
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "GRANT schema ON 'mall' TO 'alice';"
––– output –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=alicepass123 mysql -ualice -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE TABLE mall(id bigint) shards='2' rf='1';"; echo $?
––– output –––
0
––– input –––
sleep 2; echo done
––– output –––
done
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=alicepass123 mysql -ualice -h0 -P9306 -e "SHOW SHARDING STATUS;" | grep -c mall
––– output –––
0
––– comment –––
––– 6a. read grant adds visibility: alice sees her table, not the foreign one –––
EXPECTED: 2 shard rows for mall, none for shop, active master
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "GRANT read ON 'mall' TO 'alice';"
––– output –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=alicepass123 mysql -ualice -h0 -P9306 -e "SHOW SHARDING STATUS;" | grep -c mall
––– output –––
2
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=alicepass123 mysql -ualice -h0 -P9306 -e "SHOW SHARDING STATUS;" | grep -c shop
––– output –––
0
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=alicepass123 mysql -ualice -h0 -P9306 -e "SHOW SHARDING MASTER;" | grep -c active
––– output –––
1
––– comment –––
––– 7. alice drops her own table but not the foreign one –––
EXPECTED: mall dropped; shop denied by the daemon
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=alicepass123 mysql -ualice -h0 -P9306 -e "DROP TABLE mall;"; echo $?
––– output –––
0
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=alicepass123 mysql -ualice -h0 -P9306 -e "DROP TABLE shop;"
––– output –––
ERROR 1045 (42000) at line 1: Permission denied for user 'alice'
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "SHOW SHARDING STATUS;" | grep -c mall
––– output –––
0
